Marks: N/A means this feature is prohibited to set when this IO type is selected

IO_Type: INTERNAL means use internal VREF voltage for INR mode
Inout Mode: VREF1_LOAD means use external input VREF voltage for INR mode
Drive: 1 pin on this bank IO Type must be set to VREF1_LOAD input mode.

IO_Type: OFF means there is no resister on single IO
Inout Mode: ON means there are both 100ohm pull up and 100ohm pull down resister on single IO.

IO_Type: OFF means there is no differential resister on IO Pair
Inout Mode: ON means there is a 100ohm resister between IO Pair(A and B).
